query: I’d like to report a scam incident. It was a phishing attempt I encountered through SMS. The incident took place on April 7, 2025. I clicked a link after receiving an SMS about some bills. Yes, I was directed to a site that looked similar to DBS's official portal. There, I was prompted to enter my card credentials to verify my identity. I didn't realize it was a fake site until it was too late. I lost $225.90. It was transferred to a Citibank account after my credentials were compromised. This happened right after I entered my card information on that site. The account where the money was transferred belongs to a beneficiary with the identifier 15594078 at Citibank. The scammer contacted me from the phone number +6591322047, but there wasn't an email associated with the scam. I hope this helps in the investigation. query: Hello, I'm here to report a scam I encountered. It happened on an e-commerce platform, Carousell, when I was trying to buy an iPhone. The incident occurred on June 22, 2025. I was really excited about the purchase, but things went south after that. I continued to communicate with the scammer through Carousell. The seller was using the moniker 'alexa83' for the transaction. I don't have any contact number or email from them. They only used Carousell to chat with me, so there were no other details exchanged as such. I made a bank transfer for the payment. The amount was $1466.85, transferred directly to the account on Carousell. It was supposed to be for the iPhone, but after I paid, the seller went silent. I made a bank transfer for the payment. query: I received a scam SMS on April 7, 2025, claiming to be from my bank. It asked me to verify something to avoid issues with my account. The SMS instructed me to verify my identity to prevent unauthorized transactions. It provided a link that looked convincing, so I followed it. The link directed me to a website that closely resembled my bank's official login page. I thought it was legitimate, so I entered my card credentials there. The link led me to a site that looked like the DBS login page, but I now realize it was a fake. I thought it was safe because it was so similar to the real thing. I entered my card credentials, including my card number and possibly my CVV. I thought I was verifying my identity for security. It's concerning how easily this happened.
